Judder is an intransitive verb which means to shake and shudder violently. If you have ever let out the clutch in a stopped vehicle without shifting from a high gear back into first gear, and if the vehicle hasn't stalled immediately, you have probably experienced juddering. It is a term most generally used to describe the behavior of machinery in extreme conditions just before failure, but it is also used to describe the behavior of a living creature, such as the scorpion, during its mating dance.